The paper deals with optimization problems related to beamforming and rate allocation in cognitive radio networks, which involve information theory (IT) and network infrastructure (NI) aspects. The paper also considers the protection of primary users, which falls under the category of systems and control (SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the decoding methods used by secondary receivers, which could be related to multimedia (MM) and machine learning (LG) sub-categories.
